<Primary>
<PrimaryPrelims>
<Title><?start-line?>A
<?new-line?>Bill

<?new-line?>To
</Title>
<Number /><LongTitle><?start-line?><Para>
<Text>Make provision for criminal sanctions against those who have entered the UK <?new-line?>illegally or who have remained in the UK without legal authority.<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
</Text>
</Para>
</LongTitle>
<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
<PrimaryPreamble>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>B<SmallCaps>e it enacted</SmallCaps> by the Queen’s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the advice and <?new-line?>consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this present <?new-line?>Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:—</Text>
</Para>
</EnactingText>
</PrimaryPreamble>
</PrimaryPrelims>
<Body NumberFormat="default">
<P1group id="p00004">
<Title><?start-line?>Presence in the United Kingdom</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Any person who is present in the United Kingdom after 30 June 2014 without <?new-line?>legal authority shall be guilty of an offence.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Any person who after 30 June 2014 enters or attempts to enter the United <?new-line?>Kingdom without legal authority shall be guilty of an offence.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00005">
<Title><?start-line?>Penalties</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>A person guilty of an offence under section 1 is liable on summary conviction—</Text>
<P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>to imprisonment for a term not exceeding 6 months;</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>to a fine which in Scotland or Northern Ireland may not exceed £5,000,</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<Text><?start-line?>or to both.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Any person who is convicted of an offence under section 1 shall be subject to a <?new-line?>deportation order unless the Secretary of State deems such a deportation order <?new-line?>to be against the public interest.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>For the purposes of subsection (2) above, a deportation order shall be deemed <?new-line?>to be in the public interest unless a certificate to the contrary has been <?new-line?>submitted by the Secretary of State to the Court.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00006">
<Title><?start-line?>Short title and commencement</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Illegal Immigrants (Criminal Sanctions) Act 2014.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>The provisions of this Act shall come into force on the day on which it is <?new-line?>passed.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
